<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id27fad220-2a4a-11ef-83f3-c9aca8a7e419" identifier="/us/usc/t45/s1344"><num value="1344">§ 1344.</num><heading> Status of Conrail after sale</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Corporation shall be a rail carrier as defined in <ref href="/us/usc/t49/s10102">section 10102 of title 49</ref>, notwithstanding this subchapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id27fad221-2a4a-11ef-83f3-c9aca8a7e419">(<ref href="/us/pl/99/509/tIV/s4036">Pub. L. 99–509, title IV, § 4036</ref>, <date date="1986-10-21">Oct. 21, 1986</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/100/1909">100 Stat. 1909</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/104/88/tIII/s332">Pub. L. 104–88, title III, § 332</ref>, <date date="1995-12-29">Dec. 29, 1995</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/109/953">109 Stat. 953</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id27fad222-2a4a-11ef-83f3-c9aca8a7e419">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id27fad223-2a4a-11ef-83f3-c9aca8a7e419"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
